headline: Snap-on (SNA): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, Snap-on has been a great trade, beating the S&P 500 by 13%. Its stock price has climbed to $384.61, representing a healthy 19% increase. This performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
